---
source: cli/tests/help.rs
expression: "help(&[\"scrub\"])"
---
Verify checksums of data and metadata.

Scrub reads all data and metadata on a filesystem and verifies checksums. This
detects hardware errors and bit rot. Scrub is typically a long-running operation
and can be paused, resumed, or cancelled. Progress and status can be queried,
and speed limits can be configured. Requires CAP_SYS_ADMIN.

Usage: scrub <COMMAND>

Commands:
  start   Start a new scrub on the filesystem or a device
  cancel  Cancel a running scrub
  resume  Resume a previously cancelled or interrupted scrub
  status  Show the status of a running or finished scrub
  limit   Show or set the per-device scrub throughput limit
  help    Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')
